gov.co |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309185456/https://www.minsalud.gov.co/Paginas/Colombia-confirma-su-primer-caso-de-COVID-19.aspx |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>As of 17 March, Colombia is denying entry to those who are not Colombian citizens, permanent residents or diplomats.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-bans/index.html |title=Coronavirus: Which countries have travel bans?|website=cnn.com |date=17 March 2020 |accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n__TOC__\n\n== Current number of cases by deparments ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable col4der\"\n|-\n! Department !! Confirmed Cases !! Confirmed Deaths !! Recovered\n|-\n|[[Bogot\u00e1]] || 2&nbsp;065 || 81 || 370\n|-\n|[[Valle del Cauca Department|Valle del Cauca]] || 797 || 48 || 122\n|-\n|[[Antioquia Department|Antioquia]] || 447 || 3 || 137\n|-\n|[[Bol\u00edvar Department|Bol\u00edvar]] || 220 || 20 || 58\n|-\n|[[Cundinamarca Department|Cundinamarca]] || 187 || 9 || 151\n|-\n|[[Meta Department|Meta]] || 162 || 4 || 10\n|-\n|[[Risaralda Department|Risaralda]] || 148 || 5 || 129\n|-\n|[[Magdalena Department|Magdalena]] || 147 || 2 || 1\n|-\n|[[Atl\u00e1ntico Department|Atl\u00e1ntico]] || 134 || 2 || 8\n|-\n|[[Huila Department|Huila]] || 82 || 5 || 26\n|-\n|[[Nari\u00f1o Department|Nari\u00f1o]] || 79 || 6 || 11\n|-\n|[[Norte de Santander Department|Norte de Santander]] || 60 || 4 || 19\n|-\n|[[Quind\u00edo Department|Quind\u00edo]] || 55 || 2 || 19\n|-\n|[[Caldas Department|Caldas]] || 53 || 3 || 9\n|-\n|[[Cesar Department|Cesar]] || 42 || 2 || 17\n|-\n|[[Tolima Department|Tolima]] || 41 || 2 || 16\n|-\n|[[Santander Department|Santander]] || 37 || 2 || 23\n|-\n|[[Boyac\u00e1 Department|Boyac\u00e1]] || 33 || 1 || 7\n|-\n|[[Cauca Department|Cauca]] || 25 || 3 || 9\n|-\n|[[C\u00f3rdoba Department|C\u00f3rdoba]] || 22 || 3 || 3\n|-\n|[[Amazonas Department|Amazonas]] || 12 || 1 || 0\n|-\n|[[Casanare Department|Casanar